1
00:00:36,523 --> 00:00:37,733
And 5, 4, 3, 2...

2
00:00:38,525 --> 00:00:39,084
Action!

3
00:00:39,109 --> 00:00:39,860
Hi, Stars!

4
00:00:39,861 --> 00:00:43,072
I'm Tala Monteverde and
I'm going to tell you my...

5
00:00:43,197 --> 00:00:44,234
Cut, cut, cut!

6
00:00:44,782 --> 00:00:46,222
Sorry, Tala. Let's do one more take.

7
00:00:47,242 --> 00:00:48,177
What is going on?!

8
00:00:48,202 --> 00:00:49,546
I'm sorry, Miss Tala.

9
00:00:50,329 --> 00:00:51,429
"I'm sorry"?

10
00:00:52,039 --> 00:00:54,039
You do know that we're
currently in a shoot, right?

11
00:00:54,291 --> 00:00:55,291
Are you new here?

12
00:00:55,834 --> 00:00:56,906
You aren't, right?

13
00:00:57,711 --> 00:00:59,337
Do you know that we got delayed earlier

14
00:00:59,338 --> 00:01:01,005
because you didn't prepare the products

15
00:01:01,006 --> 00:01:02,591
and now you're ruining the shoot?

16
00:01:03,217 --> 00:01:04,217
What the heck!

17
00:01:04,885 --> 00:01:06,136
How incompetent!

18
00:01:06,804 --> 00:01:08,484
You're already stupid,
and you're weak too!

19
00:01:09,098 --> 00:01:10,098
You're fired.

20
00:01:10,474 --> 00:01:11,558
You're so arrogant.

21
00:01:11,642 --> 00:01:12,935
Just because you're a celebrity?

22
00:01:14,269 --> 00:01:15,269
Excuse you.

23
00:01:15,729 --> 00:01:16,729
I'm not arrogant.

24
00:01:16,939 --> 00:01:20,025
I just happen to respect and value the time
of everyone here.

25
00:01:20,859 --> 00:01:22,299
Aren't you ashamed in front of them?

26
00:01:22,403 --> 00:01:24,863
You're wasting their time, including mine!

27
00:01:25,572 --> 00:01:27,574
You will fail too, mark my words!

28
00:01:27,658 --> 00:01:28,992
Just wait until your day comes!

29
00:01:30,077 --> 00:01:31,178
Can't wait!

30
00:01:31,203 --> 00:01:32,203
As if.

31
00:01:33,580 --> 00:01:35,600
How dare she threaten me.
Who does she think she is?

32
00:01:35,624 --> 00:01:36,729
She has a lot of nerve!

33
00:01:36,792 --> 00:01:39,169
Sorry, everyone. I'm so sorry.

34
00:01:39,730 --> 00:01:41,078
Shall we take it from
the top? Is that okay?

35
00:01:41,102 --> 00:01:41,856
Yes, yes, yes.

36
00:01:41,880 --> 00:01:43,424
- Okay.
- Relax, relax, relax.

37
00:01:43,882 --> 00:01:45,542
Okay. Camera are rolling.

38
00:01:48,554 --> 00:01:49,680
5, 4, 3, 2...

39
00:01:50,806 --> 00:01:51,657
Action!

40
00:01:51,682 --> 00:01:54,393
Success isn't just about
getting what you want.

41
00:01:55,602 --> 00:01:56,729
It's about

42
00:01:56,754 --> 00:01:59,423
becoming the woman
everyone wishes they could be.

43
00:02:00,111 --> 00:02:02,073
The glitz, the glamour.

44
00:02:03,071 --> 00:02:05,198
The life people only dream about.

45
00:02:06,029 --> 00:02:07,167
For some people,

46
00:02:07,406 --> 00:02:08,615
it's entertainment.

47
00:02:09,450 --> 00:02:10,643
For others,

48
00:02:11,326 --> 00:02:12,557
it's a escape.

49
00:02:13,787 --> 00:02:16,039
They watch you because somehow

50
00:02:16,389 --> 00:02:17,987
they get to live through you.

51
00:02:19,084 --> 00:02:21,462
So, if you're lucky enough to become
that woman,

52
00:02:22,421 --> 00:02:24,423
You do everything you can to stay heard.

53
00:02:28,927 --> 00:02:31,345
Hi, Stars! I'm Tala Monteverde,

54
00:02:31,346 --> 00:02:35,434
and this is my secret to
looking fresh and beautiful.

55
00:02:37,895 --> 00:02:38,895
Tada!

56
00:03:25,818 --> 00:03:26,610
- Hey!
- Mom!

57
00:03:26,611 --> 00:03:28,046
Where do you think you're going, huh?

58
00:03:28,070 --> 00:03:29,154
I have a side job.

59
00:03:30,155 --> 00:03:31,253
What side job?

60
00:03:31,824 --> 00:03:32,824
Huh?

61
00:03:33,075 --> 00:03:34,510
Wedding, baptism, or funeral?

62
00:03:36,161 --> 00:03:37,246
If it's a funeral,

63
00:03:37,579 --> 00:03:41,792
don't you ever bring home
food from there, okay?

64
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,377
It's considered bad luck, son.

65
00:03:44,795 --> 00:03:46,672
Grandma, it's neither of those events.

66
00:03:46,755 --> 00:03:48,066
- What is it then?
- It's a fan meet.

67
00:03:48,090 --> 00:03:49,174
Fan meet? Really?

68
00:03:49,466 --> 00:03:51,552
There's a celebrity? Who is it?

69
00:03:53,136 --> 00:03:54,112
Her.

70
00:03:54,137 --> 00:03:56,305
Wow, OMG! I know her!

71
00:03:56,306 --> 00:03:57,683
That's Tala!

72
00:03:57,891 --> 00:03:59,684
She's really popular nowadays, brother.

73
00:03:59,685 --> 00:04:01,078
She's so beautiful.

74
00:04:01,103 --> 00:04:01,995
So Latina!

75
00:04:02,020 --> 00:04:03,500
- You even did that, huh?
- Of course!

76
00:04:04,940 --> 00:04:06,483
I idolize her, son.

77
00:04:06,942 --> 00:04:10,152
Is it possible for you to
get me an autograph?

78
00:04:10,153 --> 00:04:12,155
Come on, son! Please.

79
00:04:12,295 --> 00:04:13,424
I'll try, Mom.

80
00:04:15,367 --> 00:04:17,285
My ride is here already.
I have to go, Mom.

81
00:04:17,286 --> 00:04:18,286
- Alright, son.
- Bye, brother!

82
00:04:18,287 --> 00:04:20,122
Be safe, son!

83
00:04:20,747 --> 00:04:21,747
Do your best!

84
00:04:22,896 --> 00:04:25,128
- Don't forget my autograph.
- I got it, Mom.

85
00:04:38,599 --> 00:04:39,391
Thanks, bro.

86
00:04:39,391 --> 00:04:40,391
I don't know.

87
00:04:40,934 --> 00:04:41,934
You know what...

88
00:04:42,728 --> 00:04:46,148
Maybe the personal assistant
I fired earlier is his girlfriend.

89
00:04:47,232 --> 00:04:48,232
Ride safe!

90
00:04:50,193 --> 00:04:52,613
He's the only one who
gets my angles right, Moi.

91
00:04:53,071 --> 00:04:54,155
What am I going to do now?

92
00:04:54,156 --> 00:04:55,947
I don't have a personal shooter anymore.

93
00:04:55,972 --> 00:04:56,972
It doesn't...

94
00:05:10,756 --> 00:05:11,857
What the heck?

95
00:05:11,882 --> 00:05:12,957
Are you stupid or what?

96
00:05:13,717 --> 00:05:14,717
Wow!

97
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:15,510
I'm the one being stupid,

98
00:05:15,511 --> 00:05:17,471
yet you're the one
who wasn't looking at the road?

99
00:05:19,473 --> 00:05:20,974
Then why are you blocking the way?

100
00:05:21,934 --> 00:05:22,832
Ma'am,

101
00:05:22,893 --> 00:05:24,645
can't you see that the road is wide enough?

102
00:05:26,772 --> 00:05:27,772
Plus...

103
00:05:32,319 --> 00:05:33,045
Hello?

104
00:05:33,070 --> 00:05:35,072
What are you looking for?
I'm in front of you!

105
00:05:35,564 --> 00:05:36,762
Oh. Nothing, Ma'am.

106
00:05:36,823 --> 00:05:38,491
I'm just looking for the sign that says.

107
00:05:38,492 --> 00:05:39,952
"Tala Monteverde" on the road.

108
00:05:40,285 --> 00:05:41,918
But I guess there's nothing.

109
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:44,164
So that means you don't own the road!

110
00:05:44,414 --> 00:05:45,933
You are so arrogant.

111
00:05:45,958 --> 00:05:48,502
Tala, Tala! What are you doing?

112
00:05:48,585 --> 00:05:50,504
I've been waiting for you for a while now!

113
00:05:50,529 --> 00:05:51,567
I know. I'm sorry.

114
00:05:52,089 --> 00:05:53,965
What's happening here?
Is there a problem?

115
00:05:53,966 --> 00:05:55,091
No. There's no problem here.

116
00:05:55,092 --> 00:05:57,760
Actually, we're just talking
because I bumped into him.

117
00:05:57,761 --> 00:05:59,072
I'm really sorry about that, Sir.

118
00:05:59,096 --> 00:06:01,348
I'm so sorry. Here, take this.

119
00:06:02,516 --> 00:06:03,433
Let's go.

120
00:06:03,434 --> 00:06:05,435
- The organizers are already there.
- Okay.

121
00:06:05,894 --> 00:06:09,147
Sir, please excuse her manners.
Sorry about that.

122
00:06:10,148 --> 00:06:11,775
- Let's go.
- I'm really sorry, Sir.

123
00:06:12,184 --> 00:06:13,727
Sorry, Sir!

124
00:06:15,779 --> 00:06:16,768
That's fine as well.

125
00:06:16,793 --> 00:06:19,074
I'm sorry. It's just that he
was blocking the way earlier.

126
00:06:19,491 --> 00:06:21,326
Tala!

127
00:06:23,578 --> 00:06:24,763
You're so fake!

128
00:06:24,788 --> 00:06:26,331
You act so innocent!

129
00:06:26,748 --> 00:06:28,475
I know that it's all an act.

130
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:29,793
You act as if you're kind,

131
00:06:30,085 --> 00:06:32,762
but you're actually mean!

132
00:06:35,966 --> 00:06:38,093
Ma'am, please don't act this way.

133
00:06:39,219 --> 00:06:40,821
And why do you care?

134
00:06:40,846 --> 00:06:42,223
You look like a wimp!

135
00:06:42,305 --> 00:06:43,556
That's considered as
alarm and scandal, Ma'am.

136
00:06:43,557 --> 00:06:46,223
Don't add slight
physical injury to the list.

137
00:06:47,519 --> 00:06:49,730
Sir, please help us!

138
00:06:49,980 --> 00:06:51,606
Please escort Tala inside, okay?

139
00:06:51,857 --> 00:06:53,191
Make sure that she's safe.

140
00:06:53,692 --> 00:06:55,110
Go on. Go with him.

141
00:06:56,069 --> 00:06:57,137
See you later.

142
00:06:59,197 --> 00:07:01,301
Thank you very much for your help, Sir.

143
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:04,411
By the way, My name is Moi—
Tala's manager.

144
00:07:05,579 --> 00:07:08,331
Thank you again for helping Tala.

145
00:07:08,999 --> 00:07:10,267
She's always been like that.

146
00:07:10,292 --> 00:07:12,126
She only has a sharp tongue, but

147
00:07:12,127 --> 00:07:15,130
when put in danger,
she just freezes up easily.

148
00:07:15,547 --> 00:07:17,267
That's why I'm very thankful for your help.

149
00:07:18,884 --> 00:07:20,360
By the way, what is your name?

150
00:07:20,385 --> 00:07:21,278
Uhm...

151
00:07:21,303 --> 00:07:22,303
Here.

152
00:07:22,846 --> 00:07:24,639
I'm Michael. Michael Maragtas.

153
00:07:27,225 --> 00:07:28,769
Oh my God!

154
00:07:29,227 --> 00:07:31,646
- You're the shooter for today's event!
- Yes, I am.

155
00:07:32,689 --> 00:07:33,773
Sorry.

156
00:07:33,774 --> 00:07:35,167
How about this...

157
00:07:35,192 --> 00:07:36,918
So we can make up for what happened,

158
00:07:36,943 --> 00:07:39,570
just say whatever you need and let me know.

159
00:07:39,571 --> 00:07:41,506
Don't be shy, okay?

160
00:07:41,531 --> 00:07:42,908
Anything. I will take care of it.

161
00:07:43,283 --> 00:07:43,909
Uh...

162
00:07:43,992 --> 00:07:44,618
Really?

163
00:07:44,743 --> 00:07:47,328
Can I have a signed poster of Tala?

164
00:07:47,329 --> 00:07:48,830
My Mom is a fan.

165
00:07:48,997 --> 00:07:50,707
Of course! Here.

166
00:07:51,374 --> 00:07:52,459
Thank you!

167
00:07:55,837 --> 00:07:57,262
You're just a freelancer?

168
00:07:57,672 --> 00:07:59,312
Yes. Just doing side jobs here and there.

169
00:07:59,925 --> 00:08:01,343
Ah...

170
00:08:01,968 --> 00:08:03,386
Do you want a regular job?

171
00:08:03,595 --> 00:08:04,595
What?

172
00:08:05,847 --> 00:08:09,058
Just send me your portfolio
and I'll contact you.

173
00:08:09,059 --> 00:08:10,059
Really?

174
00:08:10,894 --> 00:08:11,520
Okay?

175
00:08:11,521 --> 00:08:13,020
Yes. Thank you so much.

176
00:08:13,021 --> 00:08:13,997
You're welcome.

177
00:08:14,022 --> 00:08:16,148
Thank you again. Thank you so much.

178
00:08:16,149 --> 00:08:18,029
- Thank you!
- Just send me the portfolio, okay?

179
00:08:18,110 --> 00:08:19,653
- Bye!
- Thank you!

180
00:08:21,863 --> 00:08:23,240
This is good.

181
00:08:35,836 --> 00:08:37,754
She's so beautiful!

182
00:08:39,214 --> 00:08:42,092
Mom, you really placed Tala's poster right
next to Mother Mary.

183
00:08:42,759 --> 00:08:43,884
Grandma.

184
00:08:43,885 --> 00:08:46,555
You might as well offer
food to her poster too.

185
00:08:48,682 --> 00:08:50,308
Just leave me be, children.

186
00:08:50,892 --> 00:08:55,308
This is the first time I've received an
autograph from a celebrity.

187
00:08:57,566 --> 00:08:59,651
Thank you for the poster, son.

188
00:09:00,402 --> 00:09:02,154
That's just a poster, Grandma.

189
00:09:02,487 --> 00:09:05,031
What more if it's a video greeting?

190
00:09:07,617 --> 00:09:08,714
Yes, my child.

191
00:09:09,077 --> 00:09:10,996
My birthday is coming soon.

192
00:09:11,329 --> 00:09:12,956
Is it possible...

193
00:09:13,368 --> 00:09:17,038
to receive a video greeting
from Tala as a birthday present?

194
00:09:17,063 --> 00:09:18,063
Please, son.

195
00:09:18,545 --> 00:09:20,463
Oh my goodness, Grandma.

196
00:09:21,464 --> 00:09:22,507
Oh, come on.

197
00:09:22,966 --> 00:09:24,342
Just leave me be.

198
00:09:24,634 --> 00:09:26,010
This only happens once in a while.

199
00:09:26,011 --> 00:09:27,637
You really are something, child.

200
00:09:27,804 --> 00:09:29,848
I'm not really sure if I'll see her again.

201
00:09:30,348 --> 00:09:31,348
Let's see.

202
00:09:34,269 --> 00:09:35,478
[phone beeps]

203
00:09:38,857 --> 00:09:41,943
MOI: It's confirmed! I have a job for you.

204
00:09:46,114 --> 00:09:47,324
Got you, Mom.

205
00:09:49,868 --> 00:09:52,162
Thank you! Yes, yes, yes!

206
00:09:52,913 --> 00:09:54,539
You see?!

207
00:09:55,665 --> 00:09:56,665
"I'm sorry"?

208
00:09:57,417 --> 00:09:59,417
You do know that
we're currently in a shoot, right?

209
00:09:59,628 --> 00:10:02,297
Are you new here? You aren't, right?

210
00:10:02,547 --> 00:10:04,173
Do you know that we got delayed earlier

211
00:10:04,174 --> 00:10:05,841
because you didn't prepare the products

212
00:10:05,842 --> 00:10:07,092
and now you're ruining the shoot?

213
00:10:07,093 --> 00:10:09,179
What the f—?

214
00:10:09,721 --> 00:10:10,972
How incompetent!

215
00:10:13,683 --> 00:10:14,683
You know what, Michael?

216
00:10:14,684 --> 00:10:17,520
I love your ideas! I saw your portfolio...

217
00:10:17,521 --> 00:10:18,897
You're so talented!

218
00:10:20,023 --> 00:10:21,024
Good afternoon, Ma'am.

219
00:10:27,155 --> 00:10:28,291
You again?

220
00:10:29,783 --> 00:10:30,783
Yes, Ma'am.

221
00:10:31,326 --> 00:10:32,452
It's me again.

222
00:10:34,579 --> 00:10:35,871
- Moi?
- Mhmm?

223
00:10:35,872 --> 00:10:36,998
Have you seen the video?

224
00:10:37,624 --> 00:10:38,624
Yes.

225
00:10:38,917 --> 00:10:41,670
Now shut up and let's talk about it later.

226
00:10:42,921 --> 00:10:46,091
Anyway. Tala, this is Michael.

227
00:10:46,341 --> 00:10:47,781
He was the shooter on your fan meet.

228
00:10:48,093 --> 00:10:49,177
Your new sh...

229
00:10:49,678 --> 00:10:50,463
No.

230
00:10:50,679 --> 00:10:51,321
No.

231
00:10:51,346 --> 00:10:52,346
Him?

232
00:10:52,824 --> 00:10:53,824
No way.

233
00:10:54,307 --> 00:10:55,325
First of all,

234
00:10:55,350 --> 00:10:56,977
he's late. Do you know what time is it?

235
00:10:57,310 --> 00:10:58,310
See?

236
00:10:58,478 --> 00:10:59,478
Secondly,

237
00:10:59,562 --> 00:11:00,562
really?

238
00:11:00,689 --> 00:11:02,648
Long sleeves? In this humidity?

239
00:11:02,649 --> 00:11:04,192
Look, you're sweating profusely.

240
00:11:04,609 --> 00:11:05,609
And third,

241
00:11:06,570 --> 00:11:07,779
he looks so arrogant.

242
00:11:08,029 --> 00:11:10,490
He has a lot of nerve to show up late.

243
00:11:11,491 --> 00:11:12,658
Ouch, Ma'am.

244
00:11:13,576 --> 00:11:17,539
It really hurts to be judged
and rejected personally by Tala Monteverde.

245
00:11:18,039 --> 00:11:19,140
Miss Moi,

246
00:11:19,165 --> 00:11:21,875
you should've given me a heads up that
I will be woring with Miss Tala.

247
00:11:21,876 --> 00:11:23,562
I thought I'd be working
with a different talent.

248
00:11:23,586 --> 00:11:25,172
Then I shouldn't have
accepted the job at all.

249
00:11:25,196 --> 00:11:27,064
Maybe I'm not worthy

250
00:11:27,299 --> 00:11:32,178
of Tala Monteverde's kindness
and greatness of heart.

251
00:11:33,722 --> 00:11:34,722
Really?

252
00:11:34,762 --> 00:11:36,158
You think you're so funny?

253
00:11:36,182 --> 00:11:37,434
You aren't.

254
00:11:37,517 --> 00:11:39,102
Stop being so sarcastic.

255
00:11:41,771 --> 00:11:44,399
See, Moi? This is exactly what I mean.

256
00:11:45,025 --> 00:11:46,025
He's so unprofessional.

257
00:11:46,026 --> 00:11:47,277
Shh.

258
00:11:47,402 --> 00:11:48,569
Moi, I don't want to...

259
00:11:48,570 --> 00:11:49,596
Tala,

260
00:11:50,947 --> 00:11:52,407
I can vouch for him.

261
00:11:53,241 --> 00:11:55,743
I saw his previous works and coverage.

262
00:11:55,744 --> 00:11:57,412
And it was all good.

263
00:11:58,413 --> 00:11:59,497
And also,

264
00:11:59,998 --> 00:12:01,708
you haven't thanked him yet.

265
00:12:01,916 --> 00:12:03,918
He was the one who stopped your basher.

266
00:12:06,004 --> 00:12:07,056
And girl,

267
00:12:07,339 --> 00:12:08,939
he's already approved by the management.

268
00:12:09,341 --> 00:12:11,718
You won't find another like Sir Jess.

269
00:12:12,010 --> 00:12:13,720
Remember what the management said?

270
00:12:14,095 --> 00:12:16,056
"Post more to drown the noise."

271
00:12:16,556 --> 00:12:18,432
How will you even post

272
00:12:18,433 --> 00:12:20,060
if you don't have a shooter?

273
00:12:24,356 --> 00:12:25,356
Fine.

274
00:12:25,523 --> 00:12:26,523
Contractual.

275
00:12:26,816 --> 00:12:28,109
Thank you, Ma'am.

276
00:12:29,569 --> 00:12:30,462
Three weeks.

277
00:12:30,487 --> 00:12:31,533
Copy, Ma'am.

278
00:12:32,906 --> 00:12:33,906
No.

279
00:12:34,199 --> 00:12:35,492
Let's make it two weeks.

280
00:12:35,617 --> 00:12:37,160
Okay. Thank you, Ma'am.

281
00:12:37,648 --> 00:12:39,191
But I have some ground rules.

282
00:12:39,788 --> 00:12:40,764
Can you do it?

283
00:12:40,789 --> 00:12:41,789
Yes, I can.

284
00:12:42,290 --> 00:12:43,308
I can definitely do it.

285
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:44,333
Really?

286
00:12:47,587 --> 00:12:48,736
Thank you, Ma'am!

287
00:12:50,507 --> 00:12:52,675
- Thank you.
- Congratulations, Michael.

288
00:12:52,884 --> 00:12:54,284
- Thank you.
- I know you can do it.

289
00:12:54,386 --> 00:12:55,386
Thank you.

290
00:12:56,096 --> 00:12:57,555
Oh my God!

291
00:12:57,879 --> 00:13:00,716
This is my favorite cake!

292
00:13:02,394 --> 00:13:03,436
Look at it!

293
00:13:04,396 --> 00:13:05,230
Tada!

294
00:13:05,231 --> 00:13:07,356
It's so cute and perfect.

295
00:13:07,357 --> 00:13:08,900
I just want to eat it!

296
00:13:09,015 --> 00:13:12,212
Oh my gosh. So cute!

297
00:13:12,237 --> 00:13:13,349
Wait on a sec, Ma'am.

298
00:13:14,989 --> 00:13:18,576
Can you relax? Your stiffness
is showing on the camera.

299
00:13:32,215 --> 00:13:33,299
Rule Number 1...

300
00:13:34,342 --> 00:13:35,343
I'm your boss.

301
00:13:35,927 --> 00:13:36,861
Okay?

302
00:13:36,886 --> 00:13:38,805
My studio. My rules.

303
00:13:39,472 --> 00:13:42,872
So don't try to change the way I do things.

304
00:13:43,184 --> 00:13:44,231
Got it?

305
00:13:45,395 --> 00:13:46,395
Ma'am!

306
00:13:55,655 --> 00:13:56,655
Get.

307
00:13:56,906 --> 00:13:57,365
Off.

308
00:13:57,740 --> 00:13:58,740
Me!

309
00:14:04,706 --> 00:14:06,332
"Get off me!"

310
00:14:21,139 --> 00:14:22,139
Yes, daddy.

311
00:14:23,641 --> 00:14:25,018
I'm fine. I'm happy.

312
00:14:25,518 --> 00:14:26,518
Of course.

313
00:14:28,062 --> 00:14:29,771
It's just that I'm really busy with work.

314
00:14:29,772 --> 00:14:30,772
You know how work can be.

315
00:14:30,857 --> 00:14:31,857
The usual.

316
00:14:32,734 --> 00:14:35,236
There are brand deals,
collabs, and all that stuff.

317
00:14:35,403 --> 00:14:37,572
I'm actually really busy today.
I have a lot to finish.

318
00:14:41,993 --> 00:14:42,994
Rule Number 2...

319
00:14:46,915 --> 00:14:48,041
Whatever you hear,

320
00:14:49,501 --> 00:14:50,501
Whatever you see,

321
00:14:51,711 --> 00:14:52,962
All confidential.

322
00:14:53,838 --> 00:14:54,838
Got it?

323
00:14:56,049 --> 00:14:57,049
Uhm...

324
00:14:57,509 --> 00:14:58,509
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

325
00:14:58,885 --> 00:15:00,428
It's not my intention to eavesdrop.

326
00:15:02,096 --> 00:15:03,096
Whatever.

327
00:15:23,910 --> 00:15:24,994
Rule Number 3...

328
00:15:25,954 --> 00:15:27,163
The most important rule.

329
00:15:28,581 --> 00:15:30,500
Only capture me when I'm happy...

330
00:15:31,251 --> 00:15:33,043
because people want to live through me

331
00:15:33,044 --> 00:15:34,044
vicariously.

332
00:15:36,047 --> 00:15:37,047
Got it?

333
00:15:44,347 --> 00:15:45,827
I thought you're good at what you do?

334
00:15:47,100 --> 00:15:48,810
Why are your shots terrible?

335
00:15:49,561 --> 00:15:50,561
It's good, Ma'am.

336
00:15:51,354 --> 00:15:52,354
Good?

337
00:15:53,273 --> 00:15:54,273
What's good about them?

338
00:15:55,567 --> 00:15:57,652
There really isn't any
photo where I'm smiling.

339
00:15:59,362 --> 00:16:01,531
What can't you
understand? Didn't I tell you

340
00:16:01,906 --> 00:16:03,824
to only capture me when I'm happy because

341
00:16:03,825 --> 00:16:06,411
people want to live through me vicariously.

342
00:16:07,662 --> 00:16:09,956
Vulnerability is not my branding.

343
00:16:11,499 --> 00:16:13,585
But at least those pictures humanized you.

344
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:17,088
With more emotions.

345
00:16:22,719 --> 00:16:23,719
More real.

346
00:16:25,138 --> 00:16:26,138
Not fake.

347
00:16:27,432 --> 00:16:28,432
Right?

348
00:16:32,604 --> 00:16:33,604
You know what?

349
00:16:37,942 --> 00:16:39,986
We should finish this brand collab

350
00:16:40,486 --> 00:16:41,486
tomorrow.

351
00:16:42,488 --> 00:16:45,158
Let's finish this and after that,
we can call it quits.

352
00:16:47,076 --> 00:16:48,077
You don't have to worry.

353
00:16:49,621 --> 00:16:51,831
I'll still pay for the entire month.

354
00:17:06,554 --> 00:17:07,889
[phone beeps]

355
00:17:17,398 --> 00:17:18,398
Tala, it's okay.

356
00:17:18,900 --> 00:17:20,485
It's part of being an influencer.

357
00:17:21,152 --> 00:17:22,152
It's okay.

358
00:17:23,071 --> 00:17:24,614
Remember what management said...

359
00:17:25,198 --> 00:17:26,866
"Ignore, delete, forget."

360
00:17:27,450 --> 00:17:29,118
"Ignore, delete, forget."

361
00:17:29,661 --> 00:17:31,287
"Ignore, delete, forget."

362
00:17:34,415 --> 00:17:35,875
Comfort is key.

363
00:17:36,417 --> 00:17:37,710
- The—
- [phone rings]

364
00:17:38,252 --> 00:17:40,338
I am sorry, Ma'am.
Just hold on for a moment.

365
00:17:41,881 --> 00:17:44,300
Let's roll again. 3, 2, 1, action!

366
00:17:44,967 --> 00:17:46,427
Comfort is key.

367
00:17:46,552 --> 00:17:47,719
- The—
- [phone beeps]

368
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:48,720
Ma'am,

369
00:17:49,764 --> 00:17:51,814
What is it, Michael?
Just answer the call.

370
00:17:51,838 --> 00:17:53,434
JAJA: Uncle, where are you?

371
00:17:54,477 --> 00:17:55,395
It's okay.

372
00:17:55,396 --> 00:17:57,230
- Is it?
- I'm really sorry, Ma'am.

373
00:17:59,399 --> 00:18:00,919
- You already handled it?
- Yes, Ma'am.

374
00:18:01,484 --> 00:18:02,818
Comfort is key.

375
00:18:02,819 --> 00:18:04,404
That's why wherever you go,

376
00:18:04,696 --> 00:18:07,115
what you wear should also move with you.

377
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:09,951
It should be light,
breathable, and stylish.

378
00:18:11,536 --> 00:18:13,871
It should be available from...

379
00:18:14,414 --> 00:18:18,042
Morning runs to afternoon errands,

380
00:18:18,167 --> 00:18:19,727
You shouldn't have to choose between...

381
00:18:20,044 --> 00:18:21,044
Ma'am!

382
00:18:29,846 --> 00:18:30,846
You're okay.

383
00:18:31,639 --> 00:18:32,778
You're safe, Ma'am.

384
00:18:54,328 --> 00:18:55,328
Ma'am.

385
00:18:56,581 --> 00:18:57,581
Are you okay?

386
00:19:02,545 --> 00:19:03,796
I am right here, Ma'am.

387
00:19:04,422 --> 00:19:05,631
I won't leave you.

388
00:19:19,187 --> 00:19:20,646
Why is this happening to me?

389
00:19:24,942 --> 00:19:26,819
Am I really a bad person?

390
00:19:31,491 --> 00:19:33,409
Do you want an honest answer, Ma'am?

391
00:19:37,455 --> 00:19:38,873
Am I a bad person?

392
00:19:40,792 --> 00:19:41,792
No, you aren't.

393
00:19:43,503 --> 00:19:44,503
You're just tired.

394
00:19:45,546 --> 00:19:46,746
That's why you were irritable.

395
00:19:51,427 --> 00:19:52,947
You're always smiling for the cameras,

396
00:19:54,430 --> 00:19:55,932
always repressing your anger.

397
00:19:58,559 --> 00:19:59,559
But Ma'am,

398
00:20:01,687 --> 00:20:03,356
you're not a bad person.

399
00:20:09,904 --> 00:20:10,904
Ma'am,

400
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:13,240
I know that

401
00:20:14,867 --> 00:20:15,867
you're a strong person.

402
00:20:18,079 --> 00:20:20,373
But that doesn't mean you
should always be perfect.

403
00:20:28,798 --> 00:20:29,798
Why?

404
00:20:32,927 --> 00:20:35,555
Why are you still kind to me even though I
was so bad to you?

405
00:20:38,599 --> 00:20:41,269
Why are you still here even
though I want you gone?

406
00:20:42,979 --> 00:20:44,647
Is it because I pay you?

407
00:20:57,326 --> 00:20:59,287
My Mom always told me that

408
00:21:01,372 --> 00:21:02,373
you'll never

409
00:21:03,624 --> 00:21:04,624
be able to feel

410
00:21:04,834 --> 00:21:08,045
what others are feeling if you never put
yourself in their shoes.

411
00:21:11,173 --> 00:21:13,092
That's why after my older brother passed,

412
00:21:15,595 --> 00:21:19,515
it was me who acted as the older brother.

413
00:21:21,225 --> 00:21:22,393
I felt that

414
00:21:23,144 --> 00:21:25,187
the world isn't actually that easy.

415
00:21:29,984 --> 00:21:31,861
It turns out life wasn't that simple.

416
00:21:42,914 --> 00:21:43,914
Ma'am,

417
00:21:47,168 --> 00:21:48,711
I understand you.

418
00:21:59,472 --> 00:22:00,472
Ma'am,

419
00:22:01,390 --> 00:22:02,892
do you want an ice cream?

420
00:22:11,776 --> 00:22:13,152
Thank you again, Michael.

421
00:22:14,904 --> 00:22:16,489
For saving me and for

422
00:22:17,698 --> 00:22:18,698
listening.

423
00:22:22,161 --> 00:22:24,081
How about the ice cream?
You won't say thank you?

424
00:22:24,246 --> 00:22:25,246
I bought it for you.

425
00:22:26,249 --> 00:22:27,875
Can you stop calling me "Ma'am"?

426
00:22:28,334 --> 00:22:30,670
We're almost the same age!
You're making me feel old.

427
00:22:31,337 --> 00:22:32,337
And,

428
00:22:32,964 --> 00:22:34,006
as for this,

429
00:22:34,632 --> 00:22:36,884
don't worry. I'll reimburse it.

430
00:22:39,011 --> 00:22:40,011
There's no need, Ma'am.

431
00:22:40,429 --> 00:22:41,429
It's okay.

432
00:22:42,682 --> 00:22:43,933
But I hope somehow

433
00:22:44,850 --> 00:22:46,170
you feel a little lighter inside.

434
00:22:47,061 --> 00:22:48,771
I remember that my older brother

435
00:22:50,272 --> 00:22:53,901
used to bring us ice cream
whenever we feel terrible inside.

436
00:22:54,777 --> 00:22:56,337
We share the ice cream with each other.

437
00:22:57,405 --> 00:22:59,448
The problem might not go away,

438
00:22:59,657 --> 00:23:00,700
but somehow,

439
00:23:01,617 --> 00:23:02,617
it feels lighter.

440
00:23:05,121 --> 00:23:07,456
You know, Michael?
I hope you don't mind but

441
00:23:08,457 --> 00:23:10,042
what really happened to your brother?

442
00:23:13,504 --> 00:23:14,588
Silent killer.

443
00:23:15,214 --> 00:23:16,214
Heart attack.

444
00:23:17,591 --> 00:23:18,591
I'm sorry.

445
00:23:21,721 --> 00:23:22,722
That's why

446
00:23:23,723 --> 00:23:24,723
when he passed,

447
00:23:27,059 --> 00:23:28,728
I was left with my niece.

448
00:23:30,396 --> 00:23:32,036
I was doing side jobs from left to right.

449
00:23:32,773 --> 00:23:35,901
I need my niece to graduate college.

450
00:23:36,569 --> 00:23:37,903
That's why me and my mom...

451
00:23:39,655 --> 00:23:40,655
My mom!

452
00:23:40,823 --> 00:23:41,657
What time is it?

453
00:23:41,782 --> 00:23:42,950
Why? What happened?

454
00:23:43,534 --> 00:23:44,910
It's her birthday today.

455
00:23:45,578 --> 00:23:46,787
Then go home immediately!

456
00:23:47,663 --> 00:23:49,581
But we're not finished with the shoot.

457
00:23:49,582 --> 00:23:51,125
And isn't it my last day today?

458
00:23:53,836 --> 00:23:57,214
You know what?
Let's settle that for another time.

459
00:23:57,339 --> 00:24:01,010
I know how it feels to have
somebody special miss your birthday.

460
00:24:05,139 --> 00:24:06,682
Thank you so much, Miss Tala.

461
00:24:06,849 --> 00:24:07,849
Oh.

462
00:24:08,684 --> 00:24:09,684
I mean Tala.

463
00:24:10,227 --> 00:24:11,037
No biggie.

464
00:24:11,062 --> 00:24:11,604
Alright. Go on.

465
00:24:11,687 --> 00:24:12,687
Thank you.

466
00:24:16,734 --> 00:24:17,334
Hm?

467
00:24:17,359 --> 00:24:18,589
Can I maybe...

468
00:24:18,903 --> 00:24:21,072
ask you to do a video greeting?

469
00:24:21,238 --> 00:24:22,740
My Mom is a fan.

470
00:24:23,657 --> 00:24:24,657
Of course!

471
00:24:24,742 --> 00:24:25,742
I owe you one.

472
00:24:27,661 --> 00:24:28,746
But wait...

473
00:24:29,288 --> 00:24:30,748
Why stop at video greeting?

474
00:24:31,457 --> 00:24:32,457
Hm?

475
00:24:37,463 --> 00:24:38,047
Where's Mom?

476
00:24:38,172 --> 00:24:40,173
There— has been sulking
for a while now.

477
00:24:40,174 --> 00:24:42,801
You promised her lunch
but it's already past that.

478
00:24:42,802 --> 00:24:43,886
Happy birthday, Mom!

479
00:24:45,221 --> 00:24:47,098
Mom, I'm sorry that I'm late.

480
00:24:47,389 --> 00:24:49,058
But I have a suprise for you.

481
00:24:49,725 --> 00:24:51,602
I'm sure that you will like it.

482
00:24:52,853 --> 00:24:54,688
Just take a look at it first, Mom.

483
00:24:56,941 --> 00:24:59,692
Hi! Mommy Raphaela, Happy birthday!

484
00:24:59,693 --> 00:25:02,237
I hope that you're happy today.

485
00:25:02,238 --> 00:25:04,782
Even though Michael is a bit late.

486
00:25:05,032 --> 00:25:07,408
But Michael loves you so much.

487
00:25:07,409 --> 00:25:09,995
Thank you, son!

488
00:25:10,621 --> 00:25:12,373
Happy birthday, Mommy!

489
00:25:13,290 --> 00:25:14,290
Tala!

490
00:25:15,251 --> 00:25:16,751
Am I dreaming?

491
00:25:16,752 --> 00:25:18,629
You aren't, mommy. Happy birthday!

492
00:25:20,589 --> 00:25:21,923
Thank you, son!

493
00:25:21,924 --> 00:25:22,967
Thank you.

494
00:25:26,053 --> 00:25:27,555
Thank you, son!

495
00:25:36,438 --> 00:25:37,438
Here.

496
00:25:38,315 --> 00:25:39,315
Thanks.

497
00:25:42,111 --> 00:25:43,445
Your family looks happy.

498
00:25:44,446 --> 00:25:45,446
Happy?

499
00:25:45,906 --> 00:25:46,906
Messy happy.

500
00:25:52,121 --> 00:25:53,121
Tala,

501
00:25:53,747 --> 00:25:56,208
I know I'm not allowed
to ask personal questions but,

502
00:25:57,376 --> 00:25:58,335
Come on, Michael.

503
00:25:58,336 --> 00:26:00,463
You've broken all of my rules already.

504
00:26:00,629 --> 00:26:02,109
And now you're asking for permission?

505
00:26:03,465 --> 00:26:05,009
You almost got fired.

506
00:26:06,177 --> 00:26:07,469
So I'm not fired yet?

507
00:26:08,262 --> 00:26:09,262
Hmm.

508
00:26:09,638 --> 00:26:10,838
Since you're good at your job,

509
00:26:11,515 --> 00:26:13,350
you can actually teach photography.

510
00:26:13,934 --> 00:26:14,934
When it comes to videos,

511
00:26:15,477 --> 00:26:16,477
you're 'so-so'.

512
00:26:17,396 --> 00:26:18,397
You really are honest.

513
00:26:19,607 --> 00:26:21,107
What was your question?

514
00:26:21,108 --> 00:26:23,027
Make it quick or else I'll change my mind.

515
00:26:24,653 --> 00:26:25,653
I'm just curious.

516
00:26:27,072 --> 00:26:28,240
Where is your family?

517
00:26:32,286 --> 00:26:33,286
Well,

518
00:26:34,121 --> 00:26:36,373
my parents migrated to Canada.

519
00:26:37,750 --> 00:26:39,126
Don't you miss them?

520
00:26:40,628 --> 00:26:42,087
Sometimes. But,

521
00:26:42,671 --> 00:26:43,671
not really.

522
00:26:44,173 --> 00:26:45,173
I mean,

523
00:26:45,841 --> 00:26:48,384
growing up, they've always
been travelling for business.

524
00:26:48,385 --> 00:26:49,762
So, I'm kind of used to it.

525
00:26:55,434 --> 00:26:56,560
Uh...

526
00:26:58,687 --> 00:27:00,606
Do you know why I...

527
00:27:01,106 --> 00:27:03,901
freeze up when I'm in danger?

528
00:27:04,401 --> 00:27:05,401
Why?

529
00:27:07,988 --> 00:27:08,988
Because,

530
00:27:10,699 --> 00:27:13,911
I'm so scared of the thought
that no one will save me.

531
00:27:16,121 --> 00:27:17,331
Because I'm alone.

532
00:27:19,875 --> 00:27:20,875
You know, Tala?

533
00:27:21,994 --> 00:27:23,879
You don't need a savior.

534
00:27:24,838 --> 00:27:25,689
Sometimes

535
00:27:25,714 --> 00:27:28,008
you just have to be brave for yourself.

536
00:27:35,182 --> 00:27:36,182
Oh my goodness.

537
00:27:36,642 --> 00:27:39,019
We can be your family if you want.

538
00:27:39,728 --> 00:27:41,855
You're eavesdropping again, Mom.

539
00:27:42,231 --> 00:27:43,565
Yes, Miss Tala.

540
00:27:44,525 --> 00:27:45,525
Here,

541
00:27:45,734 --> 00:27:48,570
you're always welcome—
Doesn't matter how long you'll stay.

542
00:27:49,613 --> 00:27:50,781
Not only here.

543
00:27:51,282 --> 00:27:52,491
If you want to relax,

544
00:27:52,866 --> 00:27:55,995
my Mother left me a land in Sta. Cecilia.

545
00:27:56,203 --> 00:27:59,707
If you're tired of shoots
or want to stay somewhere else,

546
00:27:59,790 --> 00:28:01,208
or if you want to see nature...

547
00:28:02,042 --> 00:28:03,042
Mom.

548
00:28:04,003 --> 00:28:05,588
What will Tala even do there?

549
00:28:05,879 --> 00:28:08,319
There's no airconditioning
so she won't be able to sleep well.

550
00:28:11,302 --> 00:28:12,302
Miss Tala,

551
00:28:13,220 --> 00:28:14,220
is it possible

552
00:28:14,930 --> 00:28:16,240
to get a picture with you?

553
00:28:16,265 --> 00:28:18,493
Another picture? You already
have lots of pictures together!

554
00:28:18,517 --> 00:28:19,893
Come on, Michael. It's okay.

555
00:28:20,561 --> 00:28:22,980
How come it's alright
with Miss Tala but not with you?

556
00:28:23,772 --> 00:28:25,231
You're just her camera man.

557
00:28:25,232 --> 00:28:26,400
How dare you give me orders?

558
00:28:26,650 --> 00:28:27,919
- Why not?
- You really are something.

559
00:28:27,943 --> 00:28:28,943
So meddlesome.

560
00:28:29,028 --> 00:28:29,903
He really is.

561
00:28:29,903 --> 00:28:30,362
Hurry up!

562
00:28:30,612 --> 00:28:31,612
Alright, Mom.

563
00:28:31,822 --> 00:28:32,822
You're such a killjoy.

564
00:28:32,865 --> 00:28:34,742
1, 2, 3!

565
00:28:36,076 --> 00:28:37,076
Another — wacky!

566
00:28:37,745 --> 00:28:39,621
1, 2, 3!

567
00:28:42,499 --> 00:28:43,584
Thank you.

568
00:28:43,709 --> 00:28:44,709
You're ugly.

569
00:28:53,385 --> 00:28:55,345
Mommy Raphaela sent so much.

570
00:28:55,346 --> 00:28:56,597
I'm just one person anyway.

571
00:28:56,764 --> 00:28:57,222
Wow.

572
00:28:57,223 --> 00:28:58,557
My diet is going to be ruined.

573
00:28:59,433 --> 00:29:01,267
You've known her for just an hour

574
00:29:01,268 --> 00:29:02,508
yet you call her 'Mom' already?

575
00:29:02,686 --> 00:29:03,652
Well...

576
00:29:03,687 --> 00:29:05,497
She has an altar of you at our house and

577
00:29:05,522 --> 00:29:07,483
she even invited you to Sta. Cecilia.

578
00:29:08,150 --> 00:29:09,150
Are you her daughter?

579
00:29:12,655 --> 00:29:13,906
Come on. I'm just kidding.

580
00:29:14,656 --> 00:29:16,700
Why are you messing around? Are we close?

581
00:29:17,576 --> 00:29:18,577
Aren't we close already?

582
00:29:38,138 --> 00:29:39,138
Tala?

583
00:29:41,100 --> 00:29:42,101
Calm down, Tala.

584
00:29:44,228 --> 00:29:45,229
Tala, listen to me.

585
00:29:46,063 --> 00:29:47,063
Inhale.

586
00:29:47,898 --> 00:29:48,898
Exhale.

587
00:29:50,109 --> 00:29:51,819
Tala, calm down.

588
00:29:52,236 --> 00:29:53,236
Calm down.

589
00:29:55,531 --> 00:29:56,531
Inhale.

590
00:29:58,742 --> 00:29:59,742
Exhale.

591
00:30:01,026 --> 00:30:02,777
This is getting out of hand.

592
00:30:04,039 --> 00:30:06,834
I asked the management
to make a police report.

593
00:30:07,167 --> 00:30:08,167
But...

594
00:30:09,128 --> 00:30:11,338
They said that they
will talk to Myrna first.

595
00:30:12,840 --> 00:30:15,759
I'm pretty sure it's that darn
P.A. behind all of this.

596
00:30:16,677 --> 00:30:18,679
Didn't she threaten me before?

597
00:30:19,513 --> 00:30:22,057
Why can't we just bring her
to the police already?

598
00:30:22,599 --> 00:30:24,893
They said it will cause more noise.

599
00:30:25,436 --> 00:30:27,104
It will tarnish the management's image.

600
00:30:27,396 --> 00:30:28,813
What will the public think?

601
00:30:28,814 --> 00:30:31,275
That the management
can't protect its artist?

602
00:30:31,692 --> 00:30:32,692
So?

603
00:30:33,235 --> 00:30:34,695
What do you propose we do now?

604
00:30:38,532 --> 00:30:40,284
They asked you to lie low for a bit.

605
00:30:41,743 --> 00:30:42,743
What?

606
00:30:43,078 --> 00:30:44,913
What about my brand deals?

607
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:47,040
The contracts that I've already signed?

608
00:30:47,666 --> 00:30:49,106
They said they will take care of it.

609
00:30:51,336 --> 00:30:53,630
Tala, you need rest.

610
00:30:54,214 --> 00:30:55,214
Maybe...

611
00:30:56,550 --> 00:30:57,676
Out of the country.

612
00:30:58,802 --> 00:30:59,845
Moi, please.

613
00:30:59,970 --> 00:31:02,222
I really don't want stress right now.

614
00:31:02,639 --> 00:31:04,141
It's difficult to be a burden.

615
00:31:04,266 --> 00:31:06,935
What if they don't want
to pause my projects?

616
00:31:07,060 --> 00:31:08,854
There's a lot on the line up.

617
00:31:09,146 --> 00:31:11,148
Then have a vacation near here.

618
00:31:13,192 --> 00:31:15,486
Ah, whatever. No work for now.

619
00:31:20,449 --> 00:31:21,449
Tala?

620
00:31:22,659 --> 00:31:23,659
I have an idea.

621
00:31:26,371 --> 00:31:28,707
Are you up for it? I'll double your pay.

622
00:31:29,958 --> 00:31:31,168
For Jaja's college fund.

623
00:31:33,962 --> 00:31:35,047
Who is Jaja?!

624
00:31:35,438 --> 00:31:39,109
Come on. Didn't Mommy
Raphaela invite me?

625
00:31:41,094 --> 00:31:42,471
Who is Raphaela?!

626
00:31:42,846 --> 00:31:45,015
Right? Didn't she say I was welcome?

627
00:31:47,518 --> 00:31:48,518
Don't blame me, okay?

628
00:31:48,685 --> 00:31:50,770
Hey! Hold on, I'm so confused.

629
00:31:50,771 --> 00:31:52,189
What do you mean "don't blame me"?

630
00:31:52,314 --> 00:31:53,690
Where are you "welcome"?

631
00:31:55,984 --> 00:31:57,361
Hello?!

632
00:31:58,028 --> 00:32:00,447
Tala, Michael, I'm here!

633
00:32:01,990 --> 00:32:03,675
I don't understand what's going on.

634
00:32:03,700 --> 00:32:04,301
Okay?

635
00:32:04,326 --> 00:32:05,536
Can you inlude me, please?

636
00:32:06,119 --> 00:32:07,621
Can I be included?

637
00:32:14,169 --> 00:32:15,169
Oh my God.

638
00:32:18,283 --> 00:32:21,557
- Oh, Tala! You're going to enjoy it here!
- So itchy!

639
00:32:21,635 --> 00:32:23,154
It does seem like she's enjoying, Grandma.

640
00:32:23,178 --> 00:32:26,390
She is just so stubborn. I already told
her that it would be difficult for her.

641
00:32:27,224 --> 00:32:29,475
Oh, tomorrow you'll have more fun

642
00:32:29,476 --> 00:32:32,020
because we're going to
harvest some vegetables!

643
00:32:33,188 --> 00:32:36,692
- You're going to love the fresh air here!
- Hold on!

644
00:32:37,901 --> 00:32:38,610
Look!

645
00:32:38,611 --> 00:32:39,891
Oh my God. Oh my God. Oh my God.

646
00:32:43,365 --> 00:32:44,365
What happened?

647
00:32:44,533 --> 00:32:46,218
Are you okay, Tala?

648
00:32:46,243 --> 00:32:48,181
She can do it. She's the
one who insisted after all.

649
00:32:48,205 --> 00:32:48,843
I'm okay!

650
00:32:48,912 --> 00:32:49,912
I'm okay!

651
00:32:50,914 --> 00:32:52,332
May God bless you.

652
00:32:52,833 --> 00:32:53,833
Cousin!

653
00:32:54,585 --> 00:32:55,710
- You brought so much stuff.
- Can you please help me?

654
00:32:55,711 --> 00:32:56,920
Go ahead and help him.

655
00:33:00,132 --> 00:33:01,132
Alright.

656
00:33:04,261 --> 00:33:07,306
Oh my, finally got to take a vacation here.

657
00:33:17,149 --> 00:33:18,149
Tala!

658
00:33:18,442 --> 00:33:22,326
I still can't believe
that you're here with us.

659
00:33:23,380 --> 00:33:24,405
Is this real?

660
00:33:24,781 --> 00:33:27,033
Yes! This is as real as it can be.

661
00:33:27,034 --> 00:33:28,034
Really really?

662
00:33:29,286 --> 00:33:30,286
Ja,

663
00:33:30,621 --> 00:33:32,706
come and help me cook.

664
00:33:32,914 --> 00:33:35,207
It's embarrassing to Tala.

665
00:33:35,208 --> 00:33:37,210
- Come on, Grandma!
- Come now.

666
00:33:37,336 --> 00:33:39,838
Let's cook — Tala might be hungry.

667
00:33:40,589 --> 00:33:43,925
Tala, can you teach me how to become as
beautiful as you later?

668
00:33:44,426 --> 00:33:45,968
That cannot be taught!

669
00:33:45,969 --> 00:33:47,679
You're still young

670
00:33:48,096 --> 00:33:50,223
to be thinking about
those things! Goodness!

671
00:33:52,267 --> 00:33:54,147
Your mom seems really
hardworking, doesn't she?

672
00:33:54,853 --> 00:33:55,853
Hardworking?

673
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:59,650
She's the most hardworking mom to ever
grace this Earth.

674
00:34:01,568 --> 00:34:02,969
Oh, Tala. By the way,

675
00:34:03,528 --> 00:34:04,905
there are two rooms here.

676
00:34:05,113 --> 00:34:07,193
One's for mom and Jaja, and the other
one is for you.

677
00:34:07,407 --> 00:34:09,287
Clarence already cleaned
them, don't you worry.

678
00:34:10,911 --> 00:34:11,887
How about you?

679
00:34:11,912 --> 00:34:12,912
Where will you sleep?

680
00:34:13,246 --> 00:34:14,246
Here.

681
00:34:15,540 --> 00:34:16,540
No. I don't want you to.

682
00:34:17,125 --> 00:34:18,125
That's not allowed.

683
00:34:18,335 --> 00:34:19,795
This is for Jaja's college fund.

684
00:34:28,553 --> 00:34:29,820
I just thought of something.

685
00:34:30,514 --> 00:34:33,100
I was reading hate comments from
bashers last night.

686
00:34:33,517 --> 00:34:36,603
And I realized that the internet thinks
that I'm a diva because

687
00:34:36,937 --> 00:34:38,980
I'm rich and I'm classy.

688
00:34:39,940 --> 00:34:42,567
They were saying that if I were to be put
among the locals,

689
00:34:42,734 --> 00:34:44,027
I wouldn't thrive.

690
00:34:44,277 --> 00:34:47,072
And I think that this is the
right time to prove them wrong.

691
00:34:48,323 --> 00:34:49,723
You're still think about work, huh?

692
00:34:50,033 --> 00:34:51,033
Think about it!

693
00:34:51,660 --> 00:34:54,162
"A Day in the Life of Poor Tala"!

694
00:34:54,538 --> 00:34:55,430
Right?

695
00:34:55,455 --> 00:35:00,210
I could copy or actually do
what Mommy Raphaela,

696
00:35:00,335 --> 00:35:03,422
or I could even help with
the chores in this place.

697
00:35:03,547 --> 00:35:04,631
Right?

698
00:35:04,923 --> 00:35:05,716
You know that already, right?

699
00:35:05,717 --> 00:35:09,010
The usual activities or food that
people eat from...

700
00:35:09,344 --> 00:35:10,637
poor communities.

701
00:35:10,846 --> 00:35:11,846
Oh.

702
00:35:12,055 --> 00:35:13,181
Are you referring to us?

703
00:35:14,182 --> 00:35:16,268
We're part of the "poor communities"?

704
00:35:16,893 --> 00:35:17,893
The "poor"?

705
00:35:18,270 --> 00:35:19,270
No! I mean...

706
00:35:19,646 --> 00:35:21,272
That's not what I meant!

707
00:35:21,273 --> 00:35:24,692
What I mean is that people want to see
my vulnerable side.

708
00:35:24,693 --> 00:35:27,446
And I think that this
is the perfect chance.

709
00:35:27,946 --> 00:35:29,656
Tala, that's not vulnerability.

710
00:35:30,282 --> 00:35:31,282
It's scripted.

711
00:35:31,450 --> 00:35:33,075
Between us, who is the influencer?

712
00:35:33,076 --> 00:35:34,326
Why does it seem like
you know more than me?

713
00:35:34,327 --> 00:35:36,121
Tala, whose house do you think this is?

714
00:35:36,288 --> 00:35:37,648
And who do you think your boss is?

715
00:35:38,165 --> 00:35:39,165
Okay.

716
00:35:39,332 --> 00:35:41,452
After all, you're the one with five
million followers.

717
00:35:41,626 --> 00:35:42,626
Good.

718
00:35:42,669 --> 00:35:43,879
Good thing you know.

719
00:35:44,254 --> 00:35:45,254
Tala!

720
00:35:45,464 --> 00:35:46,756
- Yes, mom?
- Come outside!

721
00:35:46,757 --> 00:35:48,091
Come and help us!

722
00:35:48,258 --> 00:35:51,136
Enjoy the province life! Hurry!

723
00:35:51,470 --> 00:35:52,595
This is it!

724
00:35:52,596 --> 00:35:53,596
Go ahead and film me, okay?

725
00:35:53,597 --> 00:35:54,848
Just a sec, mom!

726
00:35:57,142 --> 00:35:58,517
Come on and hurry up!

727
00:35:58,518 --> 00:36:00,020
- Go ahead and vlog!
- You're so slow!

728
00:36:03,648 --> 00:36:04,732
Wait!

729
00:36:04,733 --> 00:36:05,733
Hold on.

730
00:36:05,859 --> 00:36:07,277
Ready? Rolling?

731
00:36:08,153 --> 00:36:10,655
A Day in My Life living a simple life

732
00:36:11,239 --> 00:36:14,326
fetching wa-ter in the province!

733
00:36:14,659 --> 00:36:16,703
Child, are you doing okay there?

734
00:36:17,287 --> 00:36:19,997
Goodness! This is just
the start of our day here.

735
00:36:19,998 --> 00:36:20,998
Cut!

736
00:36:21,166 --> 00:36:22,626
I'm fine, mom.

737
00:36:22,959 --> 00:36:24,559
- She's fine, Grandma.
- It's just heavy.

738
00:36:27,923 --> 00:36:30,883
Is there no water service provider here?
This is so heavy!

739
00:36:30,884 --> 00:36:32,676
What do you mean it's heavy? It's
almost empty

740
00:36:32,677 --> 00:36:34,136
because it kept spilling!

741
00:36:34,137 --> 00:36:35,430
I will get more!

742
00:36:35,680 --> 00:36:36,765
Alright, take two!

743
00:36:37,349 --> 00:36:38,391
Okay, take two! Rolling!

744
00:36:38,934 --> 00:36:39,934
A Day in My Life

745
00:36:39,935 --> 00:36:42,938
living a simple life here in the province!

746
00:36:43,230 --> 00:36:45,314
So, today we're going to fetch some water

747
00:36:45,315 --> 00:36:47,943
because we need water to do laundry.

748
00:36:49,861 --> 00:36:52,655
A Day in My Life living a simple life

749
00:36:52,656 --> 00:36:56,326
chopping some wood for our food!

750
00:36:56,576 --> 00:37:00,079
Look, guys. We're chopping wood

751
00:37:00,080 --> 00:37:03,124
so that we can eat food!

752
00:37:07,337 --> 00:37:08,313
There!

753
00:37:08,338 --> 00:37:09,881
I already told you to not do that!

754
00:37:10,298 --> 00:37:11,191
It hurts!

755
00:37:11,216 --> 00:37:12,216
Let me see!

756
00:37:13,093 --> 00:37:16,054
It hurts. I can't do
this — it's so difficult!

757
00:37:16,346 --> 00:37:18,066
That's because you're so stubborn. Hold on.

758
00:37:20,546 --> 00:37:23,314
I already told you to not do
that. You didn't listen to me.

759
00:37:23,937 --> 00:37:24,937
Gosh, Tala.

760
00:37:25,772 --> 00:37:27,580
Didn't I tell you that it was dangerous?

761
00:37:29,067 --> 00:37:30,067
You're so stubborn.

762
00:37:30,569 --> 00:37:33,029
You're doing everything just
for the sake of those videos.

763
00:37:41,913 --> 00:37:43,373
Shut up and film me!

764
00:37:43,957 --> 00:37:44,957
You talk too much!

765
00:37:45,876 --> 00:37:46,876
Just be careful, okay?

766
00:37:47,878 --> 00:37:48,253
Okay!

767
00:37:48,503 --> 00:37:50,380
3, 2, 1 — be careful!

768
00:37:51,006 --> 00:37:51,565
Go!

769
00:37:51,590 --> 00:37:52,883
No pain, no gain!

770
00:38:01,182 --> 00:38:02,182
Michael, hurry!

771
00:38:02,350 --> 00:38:03,350
Go ahead and film me.

772
00:38:04,686 --> 00:38:06,353
No, not there! I want mom and Jaja to
be included.

773
00:38:06,354 --> 00:38:07,354
Move to the other side.

774
00:38:07,981 --> 00:38:09,857
Oh wow! We're really included, huh.

775
00:38:09,858 --> 00:38:10,900
Ja, move aside.

776
00:38:10,901 --> 00:38:12,151
Of course they'll bring in more views!

777
00:38:12,152 --> 00:38:13,392
You really don't know anything.

778
00:38:16,031 --> 00:38:17,031
Alright.

779
00:38:17,657 --> 00:38:19,784
Do we really have to plant these?

780
00:38:19,993 --> 00:38:21,327
Are these really going to sprout?

781
00:38:21,328 --> 00:38:22,829
These seem like just stems.

782
00:38:23,955 --> 00:38:24,955
Of course they'll grow.

783
00:38:25,832 --> 00:38:27,500
Haven't you seen

784
00:38:27,792 --> 00:38:29,252
anyone planting plants before?

785
00:38:31,171 --> 00:38:32,881
This is called bag rooting.

786
00:38:33,673 --> 00:38:34,673
If it grows,

787
00:38:34,966 --> 00:38:35,966
then it can be sold.

788
00:38:36,968 --> 00:38:38,303
It's just our side line.

789
00:38:40,847 --> 00:38:41,847
Well,

790
00:38:43,350 --> 00:38:45,352
it looks like you've
never touched soil before.

791
00:38:47,604 --> 00:38:48,855
With hands as dainty as yours.

792
00:38:49,940 --> 00:38:50,940
Jaja.

793
00:38:51,566 --> 00:38:54,611
Don't tease Tala anymore.

794
00:38:56,279 --> 00:38:57,489
She's just not used to it.

795
00:38:58,615 --> 00:38:59,991
Besides,

796
00:39:01,201 --> 00:39:04,537
she's already tired from all the chores
she did all day.

797
00:39:07,457 --> 00:39:09,459
Is this what you do every day?

798
00:39:10,043 --> 00:39:11,252
Don't you get tired?

799
00:39:13,296 --> 00:39:14,589
We do get tired.

800
00:39:15,590 --> 00:39:16,590
However,

801
00:39:18,301 --> 00:39:19,783
it needs to be done

802
00:39:19,808 --> 00:39:23,520
because there is no
one else to do it but us.

803
00:39:24,933 --> 00:39:27,686
Don't you set aside time just for yourself?

804
00:39:28,019 --> 00:39:31,022
Or have a vacation just to relax?

805
00:39:33,441 --> 00:39:34,441
Of course we do.

806
00:39:35,610 --> 00:39:36,820
It's just that

807
00:39:38,279 --> 00:39:39,959
that is already considered a luxury for us

808
00:39:41,449 --> 00:39:43,576
if we spend time for ourselves.

809
00:39:46,162 --> 00:39:47,162
Also,

810
00:39:48,164 --> 00:39:50,250
we weren't born rich.

811
00:39:51,918 --> 00:39:53,712
If we are being lazy,

812
00:39:55,171 --> 00:39:56,464
we will gain nothing.

813
00:40:24,826 --> 00:40:26,535
Let me help you with that.

814
00:40:26,536 --> 00:40:27,537
Let me plant the rest.

815
00:40:29,998 --> 00:40:31,332
Are you sure, Tala?

816
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:33,131
I will try my best.

817
00:40:37,297 --> 00:40:40,049
How about this? Is
this still okay to plant?

818
00:40:40,050 --> 00:40:41,855
Yes, it's okay to plant that.

819
00:42:37,792 --> 00:42:40,503
It's amazing how your eyes don't disappear
whenever you laugh.

820
00:42:41,796 --> 00:42:43,339
You're such a workaholic.

821
00:42:45,842 --> 00:42:48,469
Gosh. It's because I get
lonely when I'm not busy.

822
00:42:51,639 --> 00:42:53,199
That's because you're a people pleaser.

823
00:42:55,059 --> 00:42:55,602
Tala,

824
00:42:56,019 --> 00:42:57,145
you're not a robot, okay?

825
00:42:58,313 --> 00:42:59,313
I know.

826
00:43:02,942 --> 00:43:06,654
Maybe I just got used to being so busy.

827
00:43:06,988 --> 00:43:09,866
I just don't want to be a
disappointment to people.

828
00:43:11,743 --> 00:43:14,495
I didn't get any validation before so,

829
00:43:14,829 --> 00:43:17,207
when I got validation from social media,

830
00:43:17,665 --> 00:43:18,124
there!

831
00:43:18,374 --> 00:43:20,418
I made a career out of it.

832
00:43:26,007 --> 00:43:27,007
What about you?

833
00:43:27,091 --> 00:43:30,094
You don't seem to have a lot
of problems. You look very chill.

834
00:43:30,720 --> 00:43:31,720
I do have problems.

835
00:43:33,306 --> 00:43:34,474
Tala, I'm a breadwinner.

836
00:43:35,266 --> 00:43:36,626
I do side jobs from left to right.

837
00:43:37,352 --> 00:43:38,894
It's because I promised my brother that

838
00:43:38,895 --> 00:43:41,105
I'll help my niece graduate college.

839
00:43:43,650 --> 00:43:46,527
You know, you're really
resourceful, Michael.

840
00:43:47,070 --> 00:43:49,072
Your future wife will be lucky.

841
00:43:55,703 --> 00:43:56,703
That's way too soon.

842
00:43:59,123 --> 00:44:00,123
What about you?

843
00:44:01,292 --> 00:44:04,671
It seems like it's hard to have a
relationship when you're a celebrity.

844
00:44:06,881 --> 00:44:08,591
Actually, it's not that difficult.

845
00:44:09,425 --> 00:44:11,552
I've had boyfriends before.

846
00:44:12,345 --> 00:44:13,846
Actually, my last boyfriend,

847
00:44:14,514 --> 00:44:19,394
he was the one who helped me start being
a content creator.

848
00:44:20,728 --> 00:44:23,564
But he was such a red flag.

849
00:44:25,108 --> 00:44:27,067
He was so violent — he hurt me.

850
00:44:27,068 --> 00:44:30,445
I had to cover up bruises with make up
before I go outside.

851
00:44:30,446 --> 00:44:31,656
That level of violent.

852
00:44:32,365 --> 00:44:33,783
That's why we broke up.

853
00:44:34,993 --> 00:44:37,287
And then I met Moi.

854
00:44:37,537 --> 00:44:38,955
You know Moi already, right?

855
00:44:44,002 --> 00:44:45,202
You didn't deserve to be hurt.

856
00:44:46,671 --> 00:44:49,090
I know. Nobody deserves to be hurt.

857
00:44:51,884 --> 00:44:54,721
I'm so tired of controlling my emotions.

858
00:44:55,847 --> 00:44:58,141
I'm tired of being a breadwinner!

859
00:44:59,434 --> 00:45:01,561
I'm tired of being bashed!

860
00:45:01,853 --> 00:45:04,022
I'm tired of having multiple side jobs!

861
00:45:07,066 --> 00:45:08,651
I'm tired of being alone.

862
00:45:11,738 --> 00:45:12,738
Me too.

863
00:45:20,163 --> 00:45:21,163
We're both tired.

864
00:45:22,498 --> 00:45:23,041
But

865
00:45:23,374 --> 00:45:24,374
we have to keep on going.

866
00:45:25,168 --> 00:45:26,168
Keep going.

867
00:45:27,920 --> 00:45:28,920
Keep going.

868
00:45:53,029 --> 00:45:53,363
Mom.

869
00:45:53,364 --> 00:45:55,907
Aren't you going to wake Tala up?

870
00:45:56,157 --> 00:45:56,966
Goodness.

871
00:45:56,991 --> 00:45:59,786
She might be too tired
from her chores yesterday.

872
00:46:00,495 --> 00:46:03,873
We need to go home before it gets dark.

873
00:46:04,248 --> 00:46:05,540
You take charge here, okay?

874
00:46:05,541 --> 00:46:06,581
- Yes, mom.
- Alright, son.

875
00:46:08,211 --> 00:46:09,712
Oh, she's already awake.

876
00:46:13,424 --> 00:46:15,176
Mom, where are you going?

877
00:46:15,551 --> 00:46:16,844
We're going home.

878
00:46:17,178 --> 00:46:19,389
Jaja has school tomorrow.

879
00:46:21,182 --> 00:46:22,308
I see.

880
00:46:23,726 --> 00:46:25,228
It's okay. You're going to survive!

881
00:46:25,853 --> 00:46:28,272
After all, you can do house chores now.

882
00:46:28,439 --> 00:46:31,317
You're a fast learner, Miss Tala.

883
00:46:33,611 --> 00:46:34,379
Alright.

884
00:46:34,404 --> 00:46:37,031
- We'll get going before it gets dark.
- Okay, mom. Be safe.

885
00:46:38,074 --> 00:46:39,241
Be good, okay? Make sure to listen well.

886
00:46:39,242 --> 00:46:40,242
Be safe, mom.

887
00:46:40,952 --> 00:46:42,494
- There's food inside, okay?
- Be safe!

888
00:46:42,495 --> 00:46:43,787
Take care of yourselves, okay?

889
00:46:43,788 --> 00:46:44,788
Yes, mom.

890
00:46:44,789 --> 00:46:46,416
Bye!

891
00:46:46,666 --> 00:46:48,106
- Ja, take care of mom.
- Yes, uncle.

892
00:47:02,515 --> 00:47:03,515
Excuse me.

893
00:47:13,609 --> 00:47:14,609
Tala!

894
00:47:15,945 --> 00:47:16,945
Tala.

895
00:47:18,406 --> 00:47:19,406
Yes?

896
00:47:21,367 --> 00:47:22,367
About last night...

897
00:47:23,453 --> 00:47:24,453
Which part?

898
00:47:26,080 --> 00:47:27,080
When...

899
00:47:28,332 --> 00:47:29,584
That's nothing, okay?

900
00:47:30,960 --> 00:47:31,960
We were just drunk.

901
00:47:32,587 --> 00:47:33,587
No meaning.

902
00:47:55,610 --> 00:47:57,737
[phone rings]

903
00:47:59,780 --> 00:48:00,381
Moi?

904
00:48:00,406 --> 00:48:01,406
Hello, Tala?

905
00:48:01,616 --> 00:48:03,451
We already talked to Myrna.

906
00:48:03,659 --> 00:48:05,995
She said that it wasn't her
that caused trouble with you.

907
00:48:06,162 --> 00:48:07,871
She just let those words slip out

908
00:48:07,872 --> 00:48:09,373
because she was deeply hurt.

909
00:48:09,874 --> 00:48:11,751
Plus, she's already in Japan.

910
00:48:12,502 --> 00:48:12,960
But...

911
00:48:12,961 --> 00:48:14,336
Wait, wait, wait!

912
00:48:14,337 --> 00:48:17,005
I'll call again later.
I just have an emergency meeting.

913
00:48:17,006 --> 00:48:18,006
Bye!

914
00:48:36,359 --> 00:48:40,279
ANONYMOUS: Unless you want to drag
them into this mess. I'll wait.

915
00:48:53,626 --> 00:48:56,295
Tala, wait. Stay here—
It's not safe yet.

916
00:48:58,420 --> 00:48:59,838
Tala, I'll go with you.

917
00:49:00,967 --> 00:49:02,384
Tala, aren't you going to talk to me?

918
00:49:02,385 --> 00:49:04,262
Will you please shut up?

919
00:49:05,638 --> 00:49:08,099
This has nothing to do with you.
Something came up, okay?

920
00:49:08,391 --> 00:49:10,393
You don't need to meddle in everything.

921
00:49:11,894 --> 00:49:13,312
Tala, I'm just worried about you.

922
00:49:13,479 --> 00:49:15,209
I don't need your worry.

923
00:49:15,273 --> 00:49:17,327
Who are you anyway? What are you to me?

924
00:49:18,901 --> 00:49:19,901
I thought we were okay.

925
00:49:20,278 --> 00:49:21,639
That's what you thought.

926
00:49:22,363 --> 00:49:23,572
Stop assuming

927
00:49:23,573 --> 00:49:25,825
and please stop following me around!

928
00:49:35,001 --> 00:49:36,001
You're fired.

929
00:49:43,259 --> 00:49:44,259
[phone beeps]

930
00:49:49,098 --> 00:49:50,850
ANONYMOUS: Think about it.

931
00:49:51,475 --> 00:49:54,812
ANONYMOUS: Unless you want to drag
them into this mess. I'll wait.

932
00:50:19,837 --> 00:50:20,837
Jace?

933
00:50:21,380 --> 00:50:21,922
Hi, babe.

934
00:50:22,131 --> 00:50:23,257
What are you doing here?

935
00:50:25,176 --> 00:50:26,176
Did I surprise you?

936
00:50:28,262 --> 00:50:29,138
Don't you "hi, babe" me!

937
00:50:29,138 --> 00:50:30,178
We broke up long time ago!

938
00:50:31,891 --> 00:50:32,892
But tonight,

939
00:50:33,684 --> 00:50:34,685
you'll come back to me!

940
00:50:36,562 --> 00:50:37,688
Hell no!

941
00:50:38,689 --> 00:50:39,689
Really?

942
00:50:41,067 --> 00:50:42,735
Is that how you should welcome me?

943
00:50:44,320 --> 00:50:46,364
You're so expensive to bring down!

944
00:50:50,201 --> 00:50:51,201
What?

945
00:50:52,203 --> 00:50:53,371
In social media, right?

946
00:50:54,330 --> 00:50:55,570
The video where you got bashed?

947
00:50:56,540 --> 00:50:58,300
You're already stupid,
and you're even weak!

948
00:50:59,001 --> 00:51:00,836
I bought that from your PA.

949
00:51:01,712 --> 00:51:02,712
You're sick!

950
00:51:03,673 --> 00:51:05,709
And the fans who kept on taunting you?

951
00:51:06,592 --> 00:51:07,677
You're also mean!

952
00:51:15,768 --> 00:51:17,436
Those all cost money.

953
00:51:19,647 --> 00:51:22,316
Jace, what's your problem?
Why are you doing this?

954
00:51:22,900 --> 00:51:24,110
Because I want to...

955
00:51:24,652 --> 00:51:25,652
punish you.

956
00:51:27,446 --> 00:51:30,366
You only broke up with me
because of your job, right?

957
00:51:31,409 --> 00:51:33,089
Because you became too much of a show off!

958
00:51:33,661 --> 00:51:35,788
Before, I was the only one
who filmed your content.

959
00:51:37,081 --> 00:51:38,624
I made you, Tala!

960
00:51:40,000 --> 00:51:41,794
But you got rid of me so easily.

961
00:51:42,628 --> 00:51:44,463
Jace, you were abusive and toxic!

962
00:51:44,880 --> 00:51:46,674
You might as well just kill me!

963
00:51:47,383 --> 00:51:49,092
That's the reason why we broke up...

964
00:51:49,093 --> 00:51:50,636
Not because I got famous!

965
00:51:51,846 --> 00:51:53,305
It's the start of your downfall now.

966
00:51:53,848 --> 00:51:55,266
And I'm the only one you need.

967
00:51:57,351 --> 00:51:58,351
It's simple.

968
00:51:59,228 --> 00:52:00,521
Come back to me, Tala.

969
00:52:00,980 --> 00:52:02,481
And everything will be okay.

970
00:52:06,068 --> 00:52:07,153
You're insane...

971
00:52:07,611 --> 00:52:08,028
Really?

972
00:52:08,029 --> 00:52:09,821
If you ever think I'll come back to you.

973
00:52:09,822 --> 00:52:11,907
I would rather freaking die.

974
00:52:12,408 --> 00:52:13,408
Why?

975
00:52:13,784 --> 00:52:15,264
Is it because you have a new shooter?

976
00:52:16,036 --> 00:52:17,840
Where is he now? Reveal him.

977
00:52:18,622 --> 00:52:19,373
Where is he?!

978
00:52:19,374 --> 00:52:20,666
I'm here!

979
00:52:23,002 --> 00:52:24,002
Gotcha!

980
00:52:27,423 --> 00:52:29,258
Tala, didn't I tell you that

981
00:52:29,759 --> 00:52:30,759
even though we're tired,

982
00:52:31,635 --> 00:52:32,635
we have to keep going.

983
00:52:32,678 --> 00:52:33,678
No one gets left behind.

984
00:52:34,764 --> 00:52:35,764
What?

985
00:52:40,311 --> 00:52:40,853
Michael!

986
00:52:40,853 --> 00:52:41,853
Give that to me!

987
00:52:41,878 --> 00:52:43,104
Let go of the phone!

988
00:52:49,987 --> 00:52:50,987
You asshole!

989
00:52:52,281 --> 00:52:53,281
Michael!

990
00:52:57,119 --> 00:52:58,370
She'll never love you!

991
00:52:58,954 --> 00:53:00,915
She's always going to choose her job.

992
00:53:01,115 --> 00:53:02,158
Her fame!

993
00:53:03,042 --> 00:53:04,876
Did you know that she only met me because

994
00:53:04,877 --> 00:53:07,317
she doesn't want me to publicize
the photo of you two kissing?

995
00:53:07,671 --> 00:53:08,756
You should listen to me.

996
00:53:09,131 --> 00:53:10,633
We're both going to end up the same.

997
00:53:11,592 --> 00:53:14,136
Tala, you don't need a savior.

998
00:53:15,387 --> 00:53:18,599
Sometimes, you just have
to be brave for yourself.

999
00:53:24,146 --> 00:53:25,146
Tala!

1000
00:53:25,272 --> 00:53:26,564
Michael!

1001
00:53:26,565 --> 00:53:27,565
Tala!

1002
00:53:27,942 --> 00:53:28,901
Tala, are you okay?

1003
00:53:28,902 --> 00:53:30,736
Michael, I'm so sorry.

1004
00:53:32,571 --> 00:53:33,572
I'm so sorry.

1005
00:53:33,739 --> 00:53:35,031
Because...

1006
00:53:35,032 --> 00:53:36,032
Are you okay?

1007
00:54:08,482 --> 00:54:09,483
Hi, Stars!

1008
00:54:09,859 --> 00:54:11,068
I'm Tala Monteverde.

1009
00:54:12,319 --> 00:54:13,319
And

1010
00:54:13,701 --> 00:54:15,906
if you've been following
me for a long time,

1011
00:54:16,574 --> 00:54:18,242
you'd probably know me as someone

1012
00:54:20,286 --> 00:54:21,787
who loves perfection.

1013
00:54:23,873 --> 00:54:24,873
But,

1014
00:54:26,458 --> 00:54:27,751
after a few days,

1015
00:54:29,003 --> 00:54:31,213
after everything I've been through,

1016
00:54:32,047 --> 00:54:33,591
I realized something...

1017
00:54:36,302 --> 00:54:38,929
perfection is not about looking perfect.

1018
00:54:39,972 --> 00:54:42,348
Perfection is not about
the perfect lighting,

1019
00:54:42,349 --> 00:54:43,434
the perfect filter...

1020
00:54:44,435 --> 00:54:46,186
It's not about pretending that you're okay.

1021
00:54:48,564 --> 00:54:51,775
Imperfection is what makes life beautiful.

1022
00:54:52,443 --> 00:54:54,361
And I've learned to enjoy it that way.

1023
00:54:56,363 --> 00:54:57,364
So this time,

1024
00:55:00,993 --> 00:55:02,620
I'm showing you who I am.

1025
00:55:04,246 --> 00:55:05,247
Without the makeup,

1026
00:55:05,623 --> 00:55:06,832
without all the glam.

1027
00:55:09,710 --> 00:55:12,421
I'm showing you myself without my shield.

1028
00:55:15,716 --> 00:55:16,884
My armor.

1029
00:55:19,595 --> 00:55:20,930
This is who I am.

1030
00:55:30,022 --> 00:55:31,357
I'm not perfect.

1031
00:55:32,066 --> 00:55:33,859
And that's perfectly fine.

1032
00:55:43,202 --> 00:55:44,202
Bye, Tala!

1033
00:55:44,828 --> 00:55:45,828
Be safe.

1034
00:55:46,288 --> 00:55:47,581
Girl, I'll go ahead.

1035
00:55:47,957 --> 00:55:48,457
Michael.

1036
00:55:48,457 --> 00:55:49,457
Bye!

1037
00:56:01,470 --> 00:56:02,470
So...

1038
00:56:03,639 --> 00:56:04,639
What's your plan?

1039
00:56:07,184 --> 00:56:08,184
I think...

1040
00:56:09,561 --> 00:56:12,564
I think I need to find myself
better without the noise.

1041
00:56:17,861 --> 00:56:19,113
Something like a retreat.

1042
00:56:20,155 --> 00:56:22,616
Somewhere isolated and far away.

1043
00:56:22,950 --> 00:56:25,369
A place with no signal, no workload.

1044
00:56:26,537 --> 00:56:27,621
Somewhere sabbatical.

1045
00:56:28,414 --> 00:56:29,414
I don't know.

1046
00:56:29,456 --> 00:56:30,791
I'm not really sure yet.

1047
00:56:35,170 --> 00:56:36,672
Is this a goodbye to our tandem?

1048
00:56:45,889 --> 00:56:46,932
Tala, what are we?

1049
00:56:52,980 --> 00:56:53,980
What am I to you?

1050
00:56:57,735 --> 00:56:58,735
Because for me,

1051
00:57:00,070 --> 00:57:01,070
I really

1052
00:57:02,740 --> 00:57:03,949
really like you, Tala.

1053
00:57:08,412 --> 00:57:09,412
Michael...

1054
00:57:09,538 --> 00:57:10,538
I understand.

1055
00:57:14,293 --> 00:57:17,254
Maybe what we want in
this world just doesn't align.

1056
00:57:19,214 --> 00:57:19,923
Maybe...

1057
00:57:20,049 --> 00:57:21,884
Maybe we both aren't ready yet.

1058
00:57:31,351 --> 00:57:32,351
Bye, Tala.

1059
00:58:00,930 --> 00:58:03,474
Alright, guys. In street photography,

1060
00:58:03,759 --> 00:58:05,561
you must not be obtrusive.

1061
00:58:05,886 --> 00:58:07,596
If you want a person to be your subject,

1062
00:58:07,930 --> 00:58:11,183
it should not be staged and
genuine interactions are a must.

1063
00:58:12,226 --> 00:58:15,229
And it's important to respect
the privacy of each person.

1064
00:58:15,479 --> 00:58:16,288
Copy, guys?

1065
00:58:16,313 --> 00:58:17,313
Yes, sir.

1066
00:58:19,858 --> 00:58:21,819
It's also important to
pick your best shots.

1067
00:58:22,444 --> 00:58:25,739
The composition should be
good, as well as the colors.

1068
00:58:26,164 --> 00:58:28,500
These should be based on the lighting.

1069
00:58:29,368 --> 00:58:29,910
Yes, sir.

1070
00:58:29,910 --> 00:58:30,452
Copy?

1071
00:58:30,452 --> 00:58:31,452
Copied, sir.

1072
00:58:31,578 --> 00:58:32,578
Okay.

1073
00:58:33,580 --> 00:58:35,791
Take some shots then
return here after an hour.

1074
00:58:36,500 --> 00:58:37,626
- Yes, sir.
- Okay, sir.

1075
00:58:40,796 --> 00:58:42,047
Don't wander too far, alright?

1076
00:59:48,822 --> 00:59:49,822
How are you?

1077
00:59:54,161 --> 00:59:55,161
Just here.

1078
00:59:55,913 --> 00:59:57,331
Teaching photography.

1079
00:59:58,123 --> 01:00:00,563
Still shooting for weddings, baptisms, and
funerals sometimes.

1080
01:00:01,210 --> 01:00:02,210
How about you?

1081
01:00:03,754 --> 01:00:04,754
Well...

1082
01:00:04,963 --> 01:00:06,632
I just returned from a retreat.

1083
01:00:07,007 --> 01:00:08,217
I really needed that.

1084
01:00:09,517 --> 01:00:12,145
And also, my parents are
asking me to come to Canada.

1085
01:00:12,930 --> 01:00:14,765
We're much better now.

1086
01:00:16,558 --> 01:00:19,019
Moi is asking me to come back to work but,

1087
01:00:20,103 --> 01:00:22,731
I'm not too sure if people still like me.

1088
01:00:28,737 --> 01:00:29,737
Tala.

1089
01:00:30,405 --> 01:00:32,574
I'm sure that the people still like you.

1090
01:00:33,784 --> 01:00:35,744
Many have been asking when will you return.

1091
01:00:36,453 --> 01:00:37,137
Wow!

1092
01:00:37,162 --> 01:00:38,914
You're more updated than I am, huh?

1093
01:00:39,289 --> 01:00:40,801
Stalker levels.

1094
01:01:01,520 --> 01:01:02,520
Tala...

1095
01:01:06,679 --> 01:01:07,679
I missed you.

1096
01:01:10,279 --> 01:01:11,405
I missed you too.

1097
01:01:12,246 --> 01:01:13,246
Really?

1098
01:01:13,532 --> 01:01:15,380
You barely even made your presence felt.

1099
01:01:18,036 --> 01:01:19,596
I needed to disappear

1100
01:01:19,621 --> 01:01:20,998
for me to return whole.

1101
01:01:22,958 --> 01:01:24,418
For me to return more prepared.

1102
01:01:28,255 --> 01:01:29,255
What about now?

1103
01:01:30,465 --> 01:01:31,508
Rae you ready now, Tala?

1104
01:01:39,057 --> 01:01:40,057
Come to think of it...

1105
01:01:41,268 --> 01:01:45,028
Why will you be ready? Who am I to you?
What even are we?

1106
01:01:48,275 --> 01:01:49,484
Before, I thought that

1107
01:01:50,040 --> 01:01:52,542
success was the glitz and the glamour.

1108
01:01:52,779 --> 01:01:54,531
The lights, the cameras,

1109
01:01:55,115 --> 01:01:56,199
the applause.

1110
01:01:57,117 --> 01:01:58,952
The millions of people watching,

1111
01:01:59,077 --> 01:02:01,137
wishing they had the life you show them.

1112
01:02:04,333 --> 01:02:05,542
I like you, Michael.

1113
01:02:06,835 --> 01:02:08,450
And yes,

1114
01:02:09,379 --> 01:02:10,379
I am ready now.

1115
01:02:11,089 --> 01:02:12,065
But now,

1116
01:02:12,090 --> 01:02:13,090
I know.

1117
01:02:13,800 --> 01:02:15,801
Success cannot be measured by

1118
01:02:15,802 --> 01:02:17,763
the number of your followers or likes.

1119
01:02:18,305 --> 01:02:20,640
Not by the number of people watching you,

1120
01:02:21,558 --> 01:02:22,558
Hello?

1121
01:02:23,185 --> 01:02:24,436
I told you, I like you!

1122
01:02:24,644 --> 01:02:25,896
I told you, I like you!

1123
01:02:26,897 --> 01:02:28,148
I told you, I like you!

1124
01:02:30,525 --> 01:02:31,568
I heard!

1125
01:02:33,445 --> 01:02:34,445
So?

1126
01:02:38,158 --> 01:02:40,153
Oh my God! I'm so sorry!

1127
01:02:40,577 --> 01:02:41,745
You're already married?

1128
01:02:43,001 --> 01:02:44,628
What do you mean married?

1129
01:02:48,919 --> 01:02:50,106
So, what is it?

1130
01:02:51,171 --> 01:02:53,173
But by the people who stay.

1131
01:02:54,299 --> 01:02:56,676
The people who see
you for who you truly are.

1132
01:02:57,803 --> 01:02:59,471
When the lights are gone,

1133
01:02:59,888 --> 01:03:00,931
the cameras,

1134
01:03:02,265 --> 01:03:03,600
and the applause.

1135
01:03:08,480 --> 01:03:10,899
You're still the one that
I want, Tala Monteverde.

1136
01:03:13,110 --> 01:03:14,736
Even if you don't say anything,

1137
01:03:16,988 --> 01:03:18,573
you're the one that I'll choose.

1138
01:03:19,590 --> 01:03:20,591
Always.

1139
01:03:25,372 --> 01:03:26,372
You know what?

1140
01:03:27,541 --> 01:03:29,876
I really don't know where this will end.

1141
01:03:31,753 --> 01:03:32,753
But I know

1142
01:03:33,463 --> 01:03:34,823
that this is what I want to start.

1143
01:03:38,385 --> 01:03:39,385
So do you think

1144
01:03:39,761 --> 01:03:40,761
that now

1145
01:03:42,097 --> 01:03:43,348
can we finally be together?

1146
01:03:44,808 --> 01:03:46,393
That is what I want to start.

1147
01:03:47,352 --> 01:03:48,352
Us.

1148
01:03:49,479 --> 01:03:50,647
No more what ifs.

1149
01:03:51,398 --> 01:03:52,482
No more maybes.

1150
01:03:54,025 --> 01:03:55,025
Us.

1151
01:03:57,404 --> 01:03:58,835
No more what ifs.

1152
01:04:04,716 --> 01:04:06,843
No more maybes.

1153
01:04:32,022 --> 01:04:34,441
And if there are people
who still choose you,

1154
01:04:39,696 --> 01:04:42,282
even if only your true self is what's left,

1155
01:04:44,367 --> 01:04:46,077
at this point of my life,

1156
01:04:48,246 --> 01:04:50,373
that's what true success is.
